Interesting!

There is an obvious "easy" way to do this - but...

I was wondering, is it possible in python to create a contraction operation that is class-level, i.e., a factory operation that uses class inspection and manipulation? Sth that allows

```python
class STLForecaster = EstimatorContract(forecaster, 
        fixed_params = {'detrend__degree' : 1},
        mapped_params = {'estimator' : 'forecast'}
    )
```
where `forecaster` is the same as above (an object, not a class)

Hello @fkiraly . Here is what I came up with from our discussion :

```python 
STLForecaster =(forecaster = {'estimator' : 'forecast'}, 
fixed_params = {'detrend_degree' : 1, 'seasonal periodicity':1}
    )
```
